Hi!


Thanks for this very nice project! I use it mainly for
programmatically setting the brightness of my monitor.


Attached find the output of

  LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d 2>&1

for my "Samsung SyncMaster 2233RZ" for both "root" and a regular user,
as well as an excerpt from Xorg.0.log and "lspci -v", both giving more
information about monitor and graphics card.


Note that there are quite some differences in ddccontrol output
between my Samsung SyncMaster 2233RZ and the one Krinn reports about
in

  http://old.nabble.com/-ddccontrol-users--monitor-infos-td32576729.html

For instance, Krinn's model reports

  Raw output: (prot(monitor)type(LCD)model(CREAMR)

while mine reports

  Raw output: (prot(monitor)type(LCD)model(McKinley)

although mine pops up this OSD window while "ddccontrol -p -c -d" is
running:

  +-----------------------------------+
  |                                   |
  | Cream                  CMO 120Hz  |
  |                                   |
  | Genesis             English       |
  |                                   |
  |     M-CM22F0BDA-1004.0            |
  |                                   |
  +-----------------------------------+

which mentions "Cream".

Also the maximum values for the registers are different (mine are
mostly 65535).


The hidden service menu on my specimen shows this (on 2011-01-24):

-------------- snip ---------------

       Service Function
 Monitor On Time :      211Hr
 Panel   Ch. No. :        0
         On Time :      211Hr
         Cycle   :      251

 PixelShift   : Off
 Country      : English
 HDCP HotPlug : Off
 HotPlug Time :    9
    LOCK      : OSD
 Scaler-MCU   : Genesis

 Version  :M-CM22F0BDA-1004.0
 Checksum :2458
 Checksum Verify :  OK

-------------- snip ---------------


IIRC, there were quite some patches posted to this mailing list -- is
there any new release of ddccontrol planned?


Regards

  Marc-Jano

