Hi

I found description for undocumented parameters.

I found MCCS 3.0 here:

ftp://ftp.cis.nctu.edu.tw/pub/csie/Software/X11/private/VeSaSpEcS/VESA_Document_Center_Monitor_Interface/mccsV3.pdf

And I figured out what parameters means:

0x02 - New Control Value  (It's not quite clear for me the purpose
                           of this register)
0x52 - Active Control  (same)
0xac - Horizontal Frequency (23164 (MSB lost?, 88700 mod 2^16 = 23164),
                             means 88.7 KHz)
0xae - Vertical Frequency  (5990 means 59.9 KHz)
0xb2 - Flat Panel Sub-Pixel Layout (Red / Green / Blue vertical stripe)
0xb6 - Display Technology Type (LCD (active matrix))
0xc0 - Display Usage Time (21 hours)
0xc6 - Application Enable Key (90, just a key for identification for
                               HP Display Assistant)
0xc9 - Display Firmware Level (512 means 2.00)
0xdf - VCP Version (514 means 2.2)
0xef - Manufacturer Specific 
0xf0 - Manufacturer Specific

So nothing interesting, most values are read only and contain expected
information.

It would be nice if VESA.xml had all indexes described in MCCS 3.0.

-- 
Audaces fortuna iuvat


